<body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=Section1>

<h1><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>DMUCS – a Distributed Multi-User
Compilation System<span style='mso-tab-count:3'>             </span><span
style='mso-tab-count:3'>                  </span><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1025" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:62.25pt;
 height:65.25pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="./dmucs-logo-large.gif" o:title="DMUCS"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=83 height=87
src="./dmucs-logo-large.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></h1>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>(for use with <a
href="http://distcc.samba.org/">distcc</a>)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'>DMUCS is a system that allows a group of users to share a compilation
farm.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Each compilation request from
each user will be sent to the fastest available machine, every time.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The system has these fine qualities:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Supports
     multiple users compiling simultaneously, and scales well to handle the new
     loads.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Supports
     multiple operating systems in the compilation farm.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Uses all
     processors of a multi-processor compilation host.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Makes
     best use of compilation hosts with widely differing CPU speeds.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Guarantees
     that a compilation host will not be overloaded by compilations.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Takes
     into account the load on a host caused by non-compilation tasks.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Supports
     the dynamic addition and removal of hosts to the compilation farm.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Works
     with distcc, which need not be altered in any way.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'>DMUCS consists of these (main) programs:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>dmucs: </span></i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>the
     “host-server”.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This application
     reads a configuration file indicating the number of CPUs and the “power”
     of each potential host in the compilation farm.<span style="mso-spacerun:
     yes">  </span>It then receives over the network:<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <ul style='margin-top:0in' type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>load
      average information from each compilation host.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>host
      requests from compile tasks that need remote hosts on which to run.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>information
      requests from monitoring applications.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>status
      requests from an administrator.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ul>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><i><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>dmucs</span></i><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'> maintains the database of hosts in the
compilation farm, and assigns hosts to compilation tasks, giving out the best
host/cpu available when the compilation task asks.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>gethost: </span></i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>a
     compilation task uses <i>gethost </i>get a host/cpu from the <i>dmucs</i>
     server.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>In general, a makefile
     will perform a compilation this way:<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>gethost distcc gcc
...<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><i><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>gethost </span></i><span style='font-family:
"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>contacts the server to get a
host, which it puts into the environment variable DISTCC_HOSTS.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><i>gethost </i>then calls the program given
to it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>After that program ends, <i>gethost
</i>releases the assigned host back to the <i>dmucs</i> server.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>loadavg: </span></i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>the
     administrator of the compilation farm must start this application on each
     compilation host.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><i>loadavg</i>
     sends the load average of the compilation host to the <i>dmucs</i> server
     periodically.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The <i>dmucs</i>
     server will “downgrade” a compilation host if the host’s load averages
     goes too high.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>monitor:</span></i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'> the
     administrator (or anyone) may use this program to monitor the busy-ness of
     the compilation farm.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It displays
     which hosts/cpus are available in the compilation farm, which hosts/cpus
     have compilation tasks assigned to them, which hosts have been made
     administratively unavailable, and which hosts are “silent” – i.e., the <i>dmucs</i>
     server has not received a load average message from the compilation host
     for a while.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1026" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:25.5pt;height:26.25pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" o:title="DMUCS"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img border=0 width=34 height=35
src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1026"><![endif]><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Installing DMUCS<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l7 level1 lfo11;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Get the latest version of DMUCS (0.6)
     from <a
     href="http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/dmucs/dmucs-0.6.tar.bz2?download">here</a>.</span></li>
</ul>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>dmucs </span></i><span style='font-family:
     "Lucida Sans"'>installs using the standard ‘configure’, ‘make’, and ‘make
     install’ steps.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>
     <i><span style='font-family:
     "Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></i></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Run </span><span style='font-family:
     Courier'>configure. </span><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>You may
     wish to use the -–prefix argument to ‘configure’ if you don’t want the
     executables, documentation, and configuration files to be installed under
     /usr/local.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Specifically, the
     -–prefix argument will tell <i>dmucs</i> where to go to look for the
     hosts-info file (/usr/local/share/dmucs/hosts-info, by default).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l6 level1 lfo17;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Run </span><span
     style='font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>make
     CPPFLAGS=-DSERVER_MACH_NAME=\\\”&lt;machine-name&gt;\\\”</span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>, where
     &lt;machine-name&gt; is where you have chosen to run the <i>dmucs</i>
     server.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>NOTE: this machine does <i>not</i> have
     to be a powerful machine – I’ve used a very wimpy Sun Ultra 5 very
     successfully.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo20;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Run </span><span
     style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>make
     install</span><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
     Batang'>.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Make sure you have your compilers in
     place on each host.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>They must all
     be found in the same directory on every compilation host.<span
     style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Also, make sure you have in place the
     distcc executables (<i>distcc</i> and <i>distccd</i>, at least).</span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Make sure the <i>loadavg</i> executable
     can be accessed and executed on each host.</span><span style='font-family:
     "Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Make sure the <i>dmucs</i> executable
     can be accessed and executed on the machine you have chosen as your server
     machine.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Create a <i>hosts-info</i> file in the location
     ‘/usr/local/share/dmucs/hosts-info’ (or, if you specified –-prefix when
     ‘configure’ing, in &lt;prefix&gt;/share/dmucs/hosts-info).&nbsp; Here is a
     sample hosts-info file:</span><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";
     mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoBodyTextIndent># Format: machine number-of-cpus power-index</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>linux-comp-1<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>       </span>4<span
style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>10<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>solaris-comp-1<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>     </span>2<span
style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>5<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>solaris-comp-2<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>     </span>2<span
style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>5<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>old-linux-comp-1<span style='mso-tab-count:
1'>   </span>1<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>4<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>old-solaris-comp-3<span style='mso-tab-count:
1'> </span>1<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>2<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>169.144.80.25<span style='mso-tab-count:2'>      </span>1<span
style='mso-tab-count:2'>         </span>2<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyTextIndent2>As you can see, the format is simple: each line is
a host's name, then the number of cpus on that machine, and then the
&quot;power index&quot; of that machine.&nbsp; If you know that some machines
are much more powerful than others, then give them higher power indices.&nbsp;
The value must be &gt;= 1. If you don't want to bother with a hosts-info file,
the system will still work, but all machines will be treated equally, and the
code will assume each machine has only 1 cpu.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>(More information on how to choose power indices is given below.)<span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Go to your host server machine and
     install and start up the <i>dmucs</i> executable.</span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>Go to <i>each</i> compilation host
     machine and run <i>loadavg </i>and start up the <i>distccd</i> daemons.&nbsp;
     The output from the <i>dmucs</i> executable should show each host being
     registered.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>(Alternatively, you
     can use the shell script <i>enable-host</i> found in the dmucs/scripts
     directory.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This will start up the <i>loadavg
     and distccd</i> programs on the host machine.)</span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo14;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans"'>In your Makefiles (or Construct or
     SConstruct files), make each compilation line look like this:</span><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.5in'><span style='font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>gethost distcc gcc ...<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo25;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Run your
     build script and see the compilations being farmed out to the fastest
     available compilation machines in your network.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1027" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:25.5pt;height:26.25pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" o:title="DMUCS"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img border=0 width=34 height=35
src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1027"><![endif]><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Tips and Tricks<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo25;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>If you
     are having problems getting DMUCS to work, first make sure that you can
     compile using <i>distcc</i>, but not <i>dmucs</i>.<span
     style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If this works, then you are most of the
     way there.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If not, then you should
     go to the <a href="http://distcc.samba.org/">distcc web page</a> for lots
     of hints on getting distcc to work.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo25;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>If you
     don’t know what values to give for the “power index” values in the
     hosts-info file, you can do this: <o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <ol style='margin-top:0in' start=1 type=1>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo25;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Set up
      distcc to run a single compilation on a single compilation host.<span
      style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo25;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Repeat this
      for the same file on each host, measuring the time it takes to compile
      each time.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo25;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Give
      your slowest machine the power index 1.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
      </span>Then, if the second slowest machine is twice as fast give it the
      index 2.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If you have a machine
      that is 10 times faster, give it the index 10.<span style="mso-spacerun:
      yes">  </span><o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo25;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>Note
      that it is often very useful to have multiple machines have the same
      power index.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>In this case, <i>dmucs</i>
      will randomly assign compilation tasks to the cpus for hosts with the
      same power index.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ol>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1028" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:25.5pt;height:26.25pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" o:title="DMUCS"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img border=0 width=34 height=35
src="./dmucs-logo-small.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1028"><![endif]><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Details on How </span><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:
normal'><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>DMUCS</span></i><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'> Selects Hosts<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo29;tab-stops:list .5in'><i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>dmucs</span></i><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'> stores
     information about each compilation host in a <i>tier</i> that equals the
     host’s power index.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Thus, if there
     are 3 machines all with power index 6, <i>dmucs</i> will put all machines
     at tier 6.</span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo29;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>When <i>dmucs</i>
     gets a host request, it randomly selects one of the cpus from one of the
     hosts in the highest tier.</span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:
     Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo29;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>When <i>dmucs
     </i>gets a load average message from a compilation host indicating that
     the load average on the machine is nearing 1.0 (or, more precisely, <i>number-of-cpus
     </i>* 1.0), <i>dmucs</i> moves the cpus for that machine from tier <i>power-index</i>
     to tier <i>power-index </i>– 1.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
     </span>Thus, if a machine at tier 6 is getting overloaded, it is moved to
     tier 5.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Subsequent <i>gethost</i>
     requests will result in allocations from remaining hosts at tier 6, thus
     lightening the load on the machine that was “downgraded”.</span><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo29;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'>If a
     machine’s load average stays above its power-index * 1.0 for more than 5
     minutes, <i>dmucs</i> will move the machine to the “overloaded” state in
     its internal database.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>No more
     compilations will be assigned to the host until its load average comes
     back down, and <i>dmucs</i> moves the machine back to its original tier.</span><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-family:"Lucida Sans";mso-fareast-font-family:
Batang'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2>Author: <a href="mailto:vic.norman@gmail.com"><span style='color:windowtext;
text-decoration:none;text-underline:none'>Victor Norman</span></a><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:Batang'><o:p></o:p></span></h2>

